## 8. Store Interface Pattern

**File**: `/Users/pc/web3/ReleaseBeacon/internal/api/projects.go`

All resources define a store interface that handlers depend on:

```go
// Interface defining all persistence operations
type ProjectsStore interface {
    ListProjects(ctx context.Context, page, perPage int) ([]models.Project, int, error)
    CreateProject(ctx context.Context, p *models.Project) error
    GetProject(ctx context.Context, id string) (*models.Project, error)
    UpdateProject(ctx context.Context, id string, p *models.Project) error
    DeleteProject(ctx context.Context, id string) error
}

// Handler only depends on interface
type ProjectsHandler struct {
    store ProjectsStore
}

func NewProjectsHandler(store ProjectsStore) *ProjectsHandler {
    return &ProjectsHandler{store: store}
}
```

This allows:
- Easy testing with mock implementations
- Swapping implementations (PostgreSQL, in-memory, etc.)
- Clear separation between HTTP and data layers

